@page "/about"

<h1>About Threebit</h1>
<p>
    Threebit is a tribute to the Spectrum, C64 and Amstrad CPC — built with the same Blazor/C# stack used
    day-to-day, as a way of building something in public rather than about it.
</p>

<h2>Roadmap</h2>
<ol>
    <li>Site shell, theming, blog, board preview — <strong>this build</strong></li>
    <li>Real backend for the message board</li>
    <li>Canvas-based game engine shared across the three machine hubs</li>
    <li>First game: a spiritual-successor clone, not a direct copy of any commercial title</li>
</ol>

<h2>A note on the games</h2>
<p>
    Recreating the actual classic titles byte-for-byte risks copyright and trademark issues, even for fan
    projects. The plan is original games in the spirit of the era — same mechanics and feel, new names,
    art and levels — or games confirmed public domain.
</p>
